OL,3,CHereditary peers to leave red benches
OL,4,Cbefore next King's Speech
OL,6,FHereditary peers will lose their seats
OL,7,Fin the House of Lords before the next
OL,8,FKing's Speech.
OL,10,FThe Lords on Tuesday accepted a final
OL,11,Fdraft of the House of Lords
OL,12,F(Hereditary Peers) Bill, marking the
OL,13,Fend of its passage through Parliament
OL,14,Fand clearing the way for it to be
OL,15,Fadded to the statue book.
OL,17,FSince 1999, 92 hereditary peers have
OL,18,Fbeen able to sit on the red benches
OL,19,Fand cast their votes in the lobbies.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1773256284
OL,3,CHereditary peers to leave red benches
OL,4,Cbefore next King's Speech
OL,6,FThe Bill effectively reduces this
OL,7,Fquota to zero.
OL,9,FHereditary peers who have not been
OL,10,Fmade life peers will no longer have a
OL,11,Fright to sit in the Lords once the
OL,12,Fcurrent parliamentary session ends,
OL,13,Fexpected later this spring.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
