CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1773256284
OL,3,CHereditary peers to leave red benches
OL,4,Cbefore next King's Speech
OL,6,FLords Leader Baroness Smith of
OL,7,FBasildon said: "This has never been
OL,8,Fabout the contribution of individuals
OL,9,Fbut the underlying principle that was
OL,10,Fagreed by Parliament over 25 years ago
OL,11,Fthat no one should sit in our
OL,12,FParliament by way of an inherited
OL,13,Ftitle.
OL,15,F"Over a quarter of a century later,
OL,16,Fhereditary peers remain whilst
OL,17,Fmeaningful reform has stagnated.
OL,19,F"We have a duty to find a way forward."
OL,26,@oD@POUwD@AOU{D@AOU{D@gO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
