PN,31804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1773256284
OL,3,CHereditary peers to leave red benches
OL,4,Cbefore next King's Speech
OL,6,FThe Cabinet minister said Government
OL,7,Fteams have "had constructive
OL,8,Fconversations" with the Conservatives,
OL,9,Fand had agreed to allocate the party
OL,10,F"a number" of life peerages.
OL,12,F"We appreciate the case that has been
OL,13,Fmade by the official opposition that
OL,14,Fthey rely significantly on the
OL,15,Fexperience of hereditary peers,
OL,16,Fparticularly on the front bench, but
OL,17,Falso in committees," she said.
OL,26,@oD@LOUpD@NO]rD@AOUrD@JO]tD@AOUyD@TO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1773256284
OL,3,CHereditary peers to leave red benches
OL,4,Cbefore next King's Speech
OL,6,FOf the 84 hereditary peers currently
OL,7,Ftaking their seats, 42 take the
OL,8,FConservative whip while 31 are
OL,9,Findependent crossbenchers.
OL,11,F"As always, it will be for the party
OL,12,Fopposite to decide which individuals,
OL,13,Feither from within or outside the
OL,14,FHouse, they wish to nominate for
OL,15,Fpeerages, subject to vetting by the
OL,16,FHouse of Lords Appointments
OL,17,FCommission," Lady Smith added.
OL,19,FThe Lord Speaker has offered his
OL,20,Fthanks to hereditary peers for their
OL,21,Fservice in the upper chamber.
OL,26,@sD@AOUyD@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
