OL,3,CHereditary peers to leave red benches
OL,4,Cbefore next King's Speech
OL,6,FLord Forsyth of Drumlean said in a
OL,7,Fstatement: "I would like to thank
OL,8,Fhereditary peers from all parties and
OL,9,Fnone for their work in the House of
OL,10,FLords over many years.
OL,12,F"Whatever views people may have of
OL,13,Fthis constitutional change, it is sad
OL,14,Fto say goodbye to friends, who in many
OL,15,Fcases have contributed significantly
OL,16,Fto debate and scrutiny and to our
OL,17,Finstitutional memory.
OL,26,@oD@LOUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1773256284
OL,3,CHereditary peers to leave red benches
OL,4,Cbefore next King's Speech
OL,6,F"Recognising their contribution is not
OL,7,Fabout party politics but acknowledging
OL,8,Fthe value of service and commitment,
OL,9,Fand I am proud to do so and to thank
OL,10,Fthem."
OL,12,FLord True, the Conservatives' shadow
OL,13,FLords leader, described the Bill as a
OL,14,F"bitter pill" for many of his
OL,15,Fcolleagues.
OL,17,F"For dozens of our fellows on this
OL,18,Fside and on the crossbenches, April
OL,19,Fwill be a cruel month of cold going
OL,20,Fbut that is how it will be," he told
OL,21,Fthe Lords.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@FO]vD@AOUvD@MO]yD@AOU|D@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1773256284
OL,3,CHereditary peers to leave red benches
OL,4,Cbefore next King's Speech
OL,6,FLord True continued: "For others, the
OL,7,Fpassage of this Bill will be a matter
OL,8,Fof high satisfaction, and that too is
OL,9,Fhow it will be, but let us treat each
OL,10,Fother's feelings with respect."
OL,12,FHe said: "So, here we are at the end
OL,13,Fof well over seven centuries of
OL,14,Fservice by hereditary peers in this
OL,15,FParliament.
OL,17,F"They helped create our Parliament and
OL,18,Fthey brought it back to life in 1660.
OL,26,@nD@VOUrD@_O]tD@JOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1773256284
OL,3,CHereditary peers to leave red benches
OL,4,Cbefore next King's Speech
OL,6,F"In this House 250 years ago, The
OL,7,FElder Pitt called for a just
OL,8,Fsettlement for the American colonies `
OL,9,Fit didn't work out very well, did it?
OL,11,F"Here in 1807, (Lord) Grenville
OL,12,Fsecured the Slave Trade Abolition Act.
OL,14,F"In 1832, (Earl) Grey moved the first
OL,15,FReform Act, and here too, the
OL,16,Fillustrious ancestor of the Duke of
OL,17,FWellington passed Catholic
OL,18,Femancipation.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31810
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1773256284
OL,3,CHereditary peers to leave red benches
OL,4,Cbefore next King's Speech
OL,6,F"Many thousands of peers served their
OL,7,Fnation here and thousands of
OL,8,Fimprovements to law were made.
OL,10,F"It wasn't all a stereotypical history
OL,11,Fof reaction in ermine. Many of those
OL,12,Fpeople, no doubt, were flawed but for
OL,13,Fthe most part, they served their
OL,14,Fnation faithfully and well.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31811
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1773256284
OL,3,CHereditary peers to leave red benches
OL,4,Cbefore next King's Speech
OL,6,F"This Bill draws a line under all that
OL,7,Fand it is drawn, but my lords, we
OL,8,Fremember them and we thank them, just
OL,9,Fas we thank and will always remember
OL,10,Fthose of our comrades in this House on
OL,11,Fall benches who are being removed
OL,12,Funder this Bill today."
OL,14,FHereditary peer the Earl of Devon, a
OL,15,Fcrossbencher, said he thought the
OL,16,FLords, Parliament and country would
OL,17,F"miss" the departing members, "not as
OL,18,Findividuals but as an essential
OL,19,Fancient thread in the complex and
OL,20,Ffragile constitutional fabric that
OL,21,Fsupports our nation".
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@WO]yD@AOUyD@FO]yD@_OU}D@TO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31812
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1773256284
OL,3,CHereditary peers to leave red benches
OL,4,Cbefore next King's Speech
OL,6,FAnd Conservative former minister Lord
OL,7,FHamilton of Epsom said: "When they
OL,8,Fhave gone, we'll be left with nothing
OL,9,Fother than political chancers like me
OL,10,Fand donors and members of the blob of
OL,11,Fone sort or another."
OL,13,FLiberal Democrat peer Lord Newby said
OL,14,Fhis "principle emotion is one of
OL,15,Frelief", adding that the decision to
OL,16,Fremove hereditary peers was "long
OL,17,Foverdue".
OL,26,@oD@YOUsD@UO]vD@EOUwD@GO]xD@]OUyD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/12
